definition.value: An alkyl cinnamate obtained by the formal condensation of the carboxy group of 3,4,5-trimethoxycinnamic acid with methanol.
An alkyl cinnamate obtained by the formal condensation of carboxy group of 3,4-dimethoxycinnamic acid with methanol.
A benzoate ester that is methyl benzoate substituted by an acetoxy group at position 4.
An alkyl cinnamate obtained by the formal condensation of carboxy group of 4-methoxycinnamic acid with methanol.
A benzoate ester obtained by the formal condensation of the carboxy group of 4-methoxybenzoic acid with methanol.
A cinnamate ester that is the methyl ester of 4-coumaric acid.
A quassinoid isolated from Quassia amara and Leitneria floridana and has been shown to exhibit antitumour activity.
A histidine derivative that is histidine in which one of the hydrogens of the alpha-amino group is substituted by an acetyl group.
